  "text": "When a graph is chordal, the minimal separators are cliques. When the graph fails to be chordal, it still may have clique minimal separators. The related graph decomposition (called clique minimal separator decomposition) has given rise to recent interest, see e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . This decomposition results in a set of overlapping subgraphs called atoms, characterized as the maximal connected subgraphs containing no clique separator.",
